author: Matthew Taylor
title: Lydia Williams howler video, W-League Brisbane Roar v Canberra United
text:
IT was the kind of routine save Lydia Williams would have made thousands of times, but in the heat of battle on Sunday it all went wrong for the Canberra United custodian.
Trailing Brisbane Roar 1-0 in their W-League clash at Suncorp Stadium, Canberra failed to adequately deal with a set piece, allowing defender Ruth Blackman the time to turn and shoot from just inside the box.
Blackman’s shot was tame at best and Williams rose to collect the ball casually, but somehow let it slip through her hands.
Canberra United goalkeeper Lydia Williams conceded an inexplicable goal against Brisbane Roar. Such was the inexplicable nature of the error that the action appeared to descend into slow motion as Williams watched the ball drop over the line and into the net, her desperate dive to clear the ball in vain.
Blackburn’s 11th minute goal doubled a lead already held by the home side thanks to Tameka Butt’s eighth minute strike. Canberra was never able to overturn the two goal deficit, with Michelle Heyman’s 39th minute effort salvaging some pride for the visitors.
The 2-1 scoreline means Brisbane shares top spot on the W-League ladder with fellow round one winners Perth Glory, with Sydney FC and Melbourne City still to face off on the opening weekend.
